      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Baseball is the only major sport that does not employ the salary cap. What's all this stuff about heart? And desire? The heart and desire were on the part of Oakland and Seattle. If the Yankees (payroll: $112 million) had lost to Oakland (payroll: $32 million), this would have been like the Dream Team losing to Ethiopia. The Yankees met the Mets with a $30 million edge.</p>
        <p>FRANK MASTRO  Wildwood Crest, N.J.</p>
      </block>
